# O-Walkie Project Memory

## Tech Stack
- Backend: Go relay server (`backend/cmd/relay/main.go`), WebSocket control + UDP audio data.
- Android client: Kotlin, foreground `WalkieService`, Opus via `kopus`, Gradle Kotlin DSL.
- Windows client: C# WPF, Concentus Opus, NAudio.
- Audio protocol: Opus mono, server handshake with protocol/version/audio params.

## Current Task
- We are stabilizing release installation and background-key functionality tradeoffs.
- Current decision: fully remove Accessibility service and background hardware PTT handling from Android app.
- Keep hardware PTT for foreground app usage and preserve core PTT/toggle behavior.

## Recent Key Changes
- Implemented server-side configurable Opus parameters (bitrate/complexity/FEC/DTX/application) and handshake propagation.
- Added and refined idle squelch shot scheduler on server:
  - timer random `10..squelch_shots` seconds (when idle),
  - shot duration random `tail_min_ms..tail_max_ms`,
  - 1s silence before and after shot.
- Changed relay startup config behavior:
  - default uses `./config.json`,
  - optional config path via first CLI argument.
- Removed Android Accessibility service path and background hardware PTT flow:
  - deleted `PttAccessibilityService`,
  - removed manifest/xml declarations and related strings/UI/settings logic.

